				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You have no problem take out the DC pet after it died aint no secret, it is only L45 mob, if you can't solo a L45 mob there is something really wrong.
<br />

<br />
But you would have it alot easier to take out your own pet if it was on the lose.
<br />

<br />
You can turn around it over and out, but this still remains true:
<br />
Basicly all pop zones have a DC pet that is "easy" to get and is put there so Enchanters and druids can DC them. This includes Elementals, even if is some cases they are harder to get (like the miniature dustrunners in PoE).
<br />
Most zones have some kind of DC pet that is animal classed (like rats in CoD, Dustrunners in PoE, Horses in PoFire, Frogs in Valor, Wrulons in HoH, Phoenixes in PoA, probaly a few I forgot).
<br />
Most of these DC pets hit pre elementals hit for 149, if you can give them weapons (not all will take weapons, most of the animals classes) will have around 150 DPS hasted.
<br />
More or less all of them have around 6-7k hp (this is kinda normal what a L45mob have).
<br />

<br />
My question is, why don't give us DC summoned and add some summoned DC pets in some more zones? I mean, elementals all have lots of mobs that normaly considered summoned (except PoWater I guess) Lots of zones can have Golems/Rock classed mobs that could be summoned (rocks allready are) and added.
<br />

<br />
If it aint overpowered for Druids, Enchanters and Necros it aint overpowrered for mages. And considered we allready have charm (at L65, but still) it fit our profile.
<br />

<br />
And if they really want a good resaon to do it, here is one. It would shut us up!!!   <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
