				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">DC pets are wonderful for groups when you can get them.  They haven't been as big of a boon on raids I've been on.  PoA raids they are not allowed in my guild.  They are KoS to other mobs and caused some issues with agro.  They are more useful in PoE because they are more plentiful and don't cause any agro issues.  Unfortunately for the enchanters and druids that get them, often lose them to enrage.  Unlike mages and beastlords, they spend more time on their non-DPS roles and can't always back the pet off at the right time.  When that happens to me, I cast another pet.  They have to wait for DC refresh.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=341305">Izarek</a>
