				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The level 51 summoning rule is not a rule.  Just a rule of thumb.  I have personally been summoned by those small, green conning rock mobs in the Grey when I was level 60 soloing there.
<br />

<br />
It's a verifiable fact that SoE can make a mob with any stats they please.  The Kromrif Recruiter in the East zone in Kael is a level 1 mob, yet he's immune to all spells regens HP like mad, and can kill any single mage pet sent against it.  It takes at least 2 61+ mage pets to overdo his HP regen and kill him.
<br />

<br />
Now, back to the original thread...
<br />

<br />
I think Dire charm pets are indeed very nice, but they are with a different balance then summoned pets.  My personal belief is that a non pet-dependant class should not get a permanent pet that is greater then the best pet of a pet-dependant class.  Charm was always balanced because of the high risk, but to a large extent, that's gone with Dire charm.  So I think Dire charm should probably be altered a bit.  Like make it slowly drain mana or something. /shrug.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
<br />
<a href="http://www.eqempyreal.com/">Empyreal</a> - Solusek Ro Server
<br />
</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
